article.headline: Stony Brook 31, Albany (NY) 28
article.story: STONY BROOK, N.Y. -- Brock Jackolski scored three touchdowns in the second half to rally Stony Brook past Albany 31-28 on Saturday in the first round of the Football Championship Subdivision playoffs. The Seawolves (9-3), who trailed 28-10 with 13:25 left in the third quarter, won their ninth straight game. They will play at Sam Houston State Saturday. Jackolski ran in a 6-yard TD and caught a 55-yard pass from Kyle Essington, pulling Stony Brook within four, 28-24, with 1:16 left in the third quarter. Jackolski then ran in a score from 11 yards with 12:40 to play. He finished with 103 yards on 22 carries, and Miguel Maysonet had 75 yards on 22 carries for the Seawolves, who outgained Albany 164-82 rushing. Dan Di Lella had 223 yards and a touchdown on 24 of 43 passing for Albany (8-4), while throwing 12 times to Ryan Kirchner for 143 yards and one touchdown.
